               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410920-name-853" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410920-name-853" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410920-name-853" type="surname" value="EDWARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410920-name-853" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT EDWARDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Oxford-street, and am a wine-merchant. On the 20th of September, about seven o'clock in the evening, I was at a fancy fair, opposite the World's End public-house, Chelsea—I felt a twitch, turned, and saw my handkerchief, part in my pocket, and the other end of it was in the prisoner's hand—I took hold of his hand and collared him—he made a violent attempt to escape, and a gang got round me—this is my handkerchief, it was entirely out of my pocket, in the prisoner's hand.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> When you turned you saw part of the handkerchief in his hand and part in your pocket? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; but before I touched his hand he had it entirely out of my pocket.</p>
